This paper discusses Bayesian optimization, which is a popular topic in machine learning and optimization. The use of probabilistic models and acquisition functions suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The mention of policy-search and control variates suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
